	<tr>
		<td width="150" align="left" valign="top" class="row1"><span class="name"><a name="105639"></a><b>Madwand</b></span><br /><span class="postdetails">Magician<br /><br /><br />Joined: 16 Mar 2003<br />Posts: 54<br /></span><br /></td>
		<td class="row1" width="100%" height="28" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
			<tr>
				<td width="100%"><a href="viewtopic.php?p=105639&amp;sid=a2974a8ff4d94d50ceb808bfc0f6afe2#105639"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Sun Nov 23, 2003 10:53 pm<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: Pets crossing zone lines</span></td>
				<td valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=105639&amp;sid=a2974a8ff4d94d50ceb808bfc0f6afe2"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>   </td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I see this currently as an impediment to travel, and as a source of irritation for groups -- having to wait for the pet owners to re-summon and buff their pets after succor / other ports. It's probably more of an irritant to the mage than to the group, who often don't see the pet as anything significant and worth waiting for. Well, they'll have to wait for me anyways; I'm not likely to take the role of a second-class wizard and start nuking without a pet being summoned and hopefully buffed. This is something that would be of major benefit to the casual / soloing mage (and the player buff vendors), as they could then take buffed pets with them to different areas. 
<br />

<br />
I think that the most serious impediments to this feature would be potentially unwarranted power increases to pet classes. But I'm having difficulty seeing them, and would appreciate if any here could think of what they might be so that we might address them further. I don't think that SOE wants us to spend the time for re-summoning and buffing pets just for its own sake. It's a non-fun expenditure of my time (and a bit of mana -- but that doesn't matter much; I'm regenning it pretty quickly with KEI and a horse) (and a reagent -- but that doesn't matter much either), and a hampering to my and my group's traveling. 
<br />

<br />
The ability to cross zone lines and escape mobs is a somewhat strange ability that comes as a consequence of the implementation / design. It is a power that's usable by all classes in some places. Adding the mage's ability to zone with a pet and come back with that same pet would be no different from a ranger or bard, e.g. zoning and coming back with a functioning bow or instrument. I really don't see the material issue here -- the mob's regen takes care of the biggest potential issue. 
<br />

<br />
Taking buffs across zones, and group buffs affecting pets, as I suggest in another thread, would be a potentially significant change. However I argue in that thread that group buffs do not significantly change power. That argument applies here too.  By this ability, the pet owner would be able to buff a pet in PoK/etc. whereever the player vendors are to be found, and then go to the hunting grounds and use the pet. This would go a long ways towards more difficult soloing. But the major change is only the location of the buffer. When those same buffs are available at the destination, there is no change in power. So again, it becomes a convenience, and an average change of power only due to that convenience.  (In fact, if the buffers are readily available at the destination, then that's even better, because farther travel is not necessary when buffs fade.  However, classes with buff abilities in exp zone do not want to be bugged for buffs outside their group -- for that reason, going to player vendors in common places is much better; they're there to sell the buffs).
<br />

<br />
As to the cost for this ability -- it could be easily generalized as Suspended Minion 3 -- you can take such a suspended pet across zones. This would add a bit of the sort of awkwardness and time delays that the game designers might want there for some reason. I would of course prefer the ability to take both active pet and suspended pets across zones, but would be quite happy with either as a start (esp. when I get to level 64).  To many players, however, it's a question as to "if they get to 64" -- for them, I would prefer that the cost be not so high-leveled.  If the feature worked with the active pet, it would be important to add another one for the suspended pet -- that could be 65 SM3 without difficulty.  The reason there, is that if a pet is being suspended, then, poofing that at zone boundary adds to the re-summoning cost just as it does for the active pet.  Moreover, that poofing currently has double cost for the backup-suspending mage -- both the active and suspended need to be re-summoned and re-buffed.
<br />

<br />
This is essentially a travel convenience, and in that regard, is one that is due. Other classes don't have to stop at each zone entrance and cast something so that they're defended or armed.   Nor do they have to do so if they zone to a bank/merchant/etc and pop back.  It's only the pet-dependent classes that have to do so. I'm sure that there is some additional development involved with this ability, and that that perhaps is the reason that the ability was not there from the start.  But, unless I'm mistaken, familiars cross zones, so much of that development has been done by now.  
<br />

<br />
I think that being able to take pets across zone boundaries would go a good distance towards making the pet classes more fun and more viable in some ways.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
