				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Its mostly technical why pets don't zone.
<br />

<br />
When BLs were first introduced, their warders were summoned similar to horses (buff icon). Every time they zoned they kept their warder, but it lost its level and all its buffs, reverting to its lowbie level state. The main reason was that servers weren't designed to handle NPCs zoning, and thus when the BL zoned it was zoned in its initial state.
<br />

<br />
The main reason BL pets were changed is to "fix" this issue. They already had to relevel their pet with their spells. Now though they simply summon it the same way mages and other pet classes do.
<br />

<br />
Recent changes to the game engine though allow NPCs to zone (remember when Grobb fell? NPCs were zoning for that script). I believe its entirely possible for pets to be coded this way now. Its just the programmers are lazy.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://members.cox.net/jmattcrews/wizardbook.jpg" align=left>[65 Arch Convoker] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=204546" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Xalmat Lunaire</a> (Human) &lt;<a href="http://www.enshadowed.net/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Enshadowed</a>&gt; ZONE: brellserilis
<br />
[56 Templar] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=816142" target="_blank" class="postlink">Eiyana Lunaire</a> (Gnome) &lt;<a href="http://www.enshadowed.net/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Evil Empire</a>&gt; ZONE: brellserilis
