Yes, programmers are lazy.  All types of people are.  But in any large software project (and even in some smaller ones) (and EQ had better be huge, considering how much money they churn in monthly and how much content they produce), programmers don't get to develop whatever they want; you have to go through marketing / support / qa / product / etc., in general management first.
<br />

<br />
By the paucity of responses here, if I was in a position of development influence in SOE, I would be tempted to conclude that mages aren't really interested in such features, and that they would be of little self-interest to SOE.  Of course, people at least as smart me would be able to think beyond that and maybe even get it done <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="Very Happy" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
