				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Having gone link dead a couple of times recently, and remembering how it used to be with link death and no rent items (oh, if you're reading, thank you SoE for giving us the 30 minute link death timeout on no rent items -- that was great improvement for the mage class), I would like to add some sort of link death timeout to pets to the wish list.  
<br />

<br />
This is less generally useful than zone crossing pets, and once it's there we would start to take the feature for granted, but I think it's worth mentioning.  Especially for those times where link and lag death are lurking and making playing generally miserable, it'd be good to not have to add resummoning and buffing pets to that cost.
<br />

<br />
The resists on rains at 10% was one issue that I and others had recently complained about.  Many thanks SoE for fixing that!  It makes rains a lot nicer to use, and I'm very happy that you're responding to such issues.   It gives me a much better opinion regarding SoE's customer service perspective.  
<br />

<br />
I also see that some others have asked for an improved sight feature for mages here, and that SoE's delivered that in LDoN.   Thanks again, SoE!  (I did the Qeynos quests for such an item, but it's good to have another, more straightforward means for this ability, and again, for SoE to respond to their customers' reasonable requests.)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
